      "id": "0cb6155d96ece7cd",
      "text": "Fear, necessary for primal survival, activates the amygdala, which then activates the hippocampus and the prefrontal cortex to contextualize and understand the fear in order to respond with action (freeze, flight, or fight) – what we might call survival processing."
